<h2 class="text-center">Trinxat (Potato, Cabbage and Bacon Hash Patties)</h2>
<div class="smaller-space"></div>
<div class="container-fluid well well-lg">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <br />
                    <img class="img-responsive" src="~/Images/Andorra/Starters/Potato-and-Bacon-Hash.webp" alt="Potato and Bacon Hash" />
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <h2 class="text-left">Ingredients</h2>
                    <br />
                    <ul>
                        <li>½ Green Cabbage (Cored and Quartered)</li>
                        <li>2 Medium Sized Russet Potatoes (Peeled and Quartered)</li>
                        <li>4 Strips of Diced Bacon</li>
                        <li>2 Minced Garlic Cloves</li>
                        <li>1 Tbsp Chopped Fresh Parsley</li>
                        <li>Salt</li>
                        <li>Pepper</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <h2 class="text-center">Method</h2>
                    <br />
                    <ol class="text-justify">
                        <li>
                            Bring salted water to boil in a large pot then add in the cabbage and potatoes, cook until tender about 30-40 minutes, once tender drain well and mash together.
                            <br/><br/>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Meanwhile cook up the bacon and reserve the fat for frying the hash, once the bacon is cooked to your liking stir it into the cabbage mash mixture and season to taste.
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Shape into patties and fry in the bacon fat until golden on each side, serve garnished with parsley and a dipping sauce such as garlic mayo or tomato ketchup.
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

