<h2 class="text-center">Espinaca a La Catalan (Andorran Style Spinach)</h2>
<div class="smaller-space"> </div>
<div class="container-fluid well well-lg">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <br /><br />
                    <img class="img-responsive" src="~/Images/Andorra/Starters/Spinach.webp" alt="Spinach" />
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <br />
                    <h2 class="text-left">Ingredients</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li>1 Apple (Cored and Diced)</li>
                        <li>2 Tbsp Olive Oil</li>
                        <li>¼ Cup Pine Nuts</li>
                        <li>¼ Cup Raisins</li>
                        <li>1 ¼ Cup of Spinach (Washed and Dried)</li>
                        <li>Salt</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <h2 class="text-center">Method</h2>
                    <br />
                    <ol class="text-justify">
                        <li>
                            Heat up the olive oil in a large frying pan to a medium heat and add in the apples, cooking until they are lightly browned.
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Add in the pine nuts stirring constantly so they don’t burn just about 30 seconds or so, then add in the raisins and stir it all together.
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Add in the spinach and give a quick stir, remove from heat, you want the spinach to just begin to wilt, do not overcook it! Add in salt to taste and serve warm in bowls drizzled with a splash of olive oil.
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

