<h2 class="text-center">Bolets Farcits (Stuffed Mushrooms)</h2>
<div class="smaller-space"></div>
<div class="container-fluid well well-lg">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <br />
                    <img class="img-responsive" src="~/Images/Andorra/Starters/Stuffed-Mushrooms.webp" alt="Stuffed Mushrooms" />
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <h2 class="text-left">Ingredients</h2>
                    <br />
                    <ul>
                        <li>8 Large Mushrooms (Washed and De-Stemmed)</li>
                        <li>6 Tbsp Butter</li>
                        <li>8 Minced Garlic Cloves</li>
                        <li>1/3 Cup White Wine</li>
                        <li>1/3 Cup Cream</li>
                        <li>1 Tbsp Flour</li>
                        <li>¼ Tsp Dried Tarragon</li>
                        <li>Olive Oil</li>
                        <li>¼ Cup Parmesan Cheese</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <h2 class="text-center">Method</h2>
                    <br />
                    <ol class="text-justify">
                        <li>
                            Preheat oven to 180 degrees and melt the butter in a large frying pan with half (4 cloves of) the garlic over a medium heat, add in the mushrooms and cook until tender.
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Whisk together the wine, cream, flour and tarragon in a small bowl and pour into the frying pan slowly and bring to a boil, stirring occasionally until the sauce thickens which will take about 5-10 minutes. Remove from the frying pan and place the mushrooms in a baking dish upside down.
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Take the remaining minced garlic and divide between the 8 mushrooms and drizzle with olive oil.
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Pour over the remaining sauce and sprinkle over the parmesan cheese, bake until the cheese turns golden brown which is around 15 minutes, serve hot with a side salad drizzled with olive oil and balsamic Vinegar.
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

