<h2 class="text-center">Embutido (Catalan Style Sausage)</h2>
<div class="smaller-space"></div>
<div class="container-fluid well well-lg">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <br />
                    <img class="img-responsive" src="~/Images/Andorra/Starters/Sausage-with-Eggs.webp" alt="Sausage with Eggs" />
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <h2 class="text-left">Ingredients</h2>
                    <br />
                    <ul>
                        <li>800g Minced Pork</li>
                        <li>8 Sliced Cocktail Sausages</li>
                        <li>2 Boiled Small Plantains (Mashed)</li>
                        <li>4 Tbsp Flour</li>
                        <li>2 Sweet Large Gherkins (Chopped)</li>
                        <li>1 Chopped Carrot</li>
                        <li>1 Small Onion (Finely Diced)</li>
                        <li>1/2 Cup Raisins</li>
                        <li>1/4 Cup Green Peas</li>
                        <li>2 Eggs (Beaten)</li>
                        <li>4 Hard-Boiled Eggs (Cut in Half)</li>
                        <li>Salt and Pepper to Taste</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <h2 class="text-center">Method</h2>
                    <br />
                    <ol class="text-justify">
                        <li>
                            In a mixing bowl mix all ingredients together (except for the hard boiled eggs and sliced sausages) and mix well.
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Place the mixture in an aluminium foil then place eggs and sausages on the middle, form a cylindrical shaped roll then wrap it tightly with cling film.
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Place it in a steamer then steam for an hour, remove from steamer and let it cool for 15 minutes, slice with foil on, remove the foil individually then serve as is or shallow fried with ketchup.
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

